post_cb({"13623322": {"ParentId": "13622781", "PostTypeId": "2", "CommentCount": "1", "Body": "<p>You could not do this anymore</p>\n<pre><code>namespace { typedef int a; ::a x; }\n</code></pre>\n<p>Note that in a subsequent <code>namespace { ... }</code>, suddenly you could. This would be horribly inconsistent.</p>\n<p>Also notice this case, with two different valid outcomes</p>\n<pre><code>namespace A { void f(long); }\nusing namespace A;\n\nnamespace { \n  void f(int);\n  void g() {\n    ::f(0);\n  }\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>With ISO C++, this calls the <code>int</code> version of <code>f</code>. With your alternative definition, it calls the <code>long</code> version.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "34509", "LastEditorUserId": "34509", "LastEditDate": "2012-11-29T10:24:57.400", "Id": "13623322", "Score": "7", "CreationDate": "2012-11-29T10:08:29.307", "LastActivityDate": "2012-11-29T10:24:57.400"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_13622781_13622781_0": {"section_id": 5482, "quality": 1.0, "length": 4}}, "n3337": {"so_13622781_13622781_0": {"section_id": 5268, "quality": 1.0, "length": 4}}, "n4659": {"so_13622781_13622781_0": {"section_id": 6917, "quality": 1.0, "length": 4}}}, "13622781": {"CommentCount": "3", "ViewCount": "324", "CreationDate": "2012-11-29T09:38:42.427", "LastActivityDate": "2012-11-29T10:24:57.400", "Title": "C++ unnamed(anonymous) namespace definition", "AcceptedAnswerId": "13623322", "PostTypeId": "1", "Id": "13622781", "Score": "7", "Body": "<p>C++03 Standard 7.3.1.1 [namespace.unnamed] paragraph 1: (and C++11 Standard also use similar definition)</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_13622781_13622781_0\">An <em>unnamed-namespace-definition</em> behaves as if it were replaced by</p>\n<pre><code>namespace unique { /* empty body */ }\nusing namespace unique;\nnamespace unique { namespace-body }\n</code></pre>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Why not is it simply following definition?</p>\n<pre><code>namespace unique { namespace-body }\nusing namespace unique;\n</code></pre>\n<p>Side question: <a href=\"http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/yct4x9k5.aspx\" rel=\"noreferrer\">MSDN</a> defines by latter form. Does it violate Standard technically?</p>\n", "Tags": "<c++><namespaces>", "OwnerUserId": "684921", "AnswerCount": "1"}});